items.definition: The amount (mass or moles) of the following pigments (chlorophyll-c1, chlorophyll-c2, chlorophyll-c1c2, chlorophyll-c3) in a known volume of any water body.

prefLabel._value: Concentration of total chlorophyll-c per unit volume of the water body

items.definition: The amount (mass or moles) of total chlorophyll-a (divinyl chlorophyll-a, chlorophyll-a, chlorophyllide-a, chlorophyll-a allomers and chlorophyll-a prime) plus total chlorophyll-b (divinyl chlorophyll-b, chlorophyll-b) plus total chlorophyll-c (chlorophyll-c1, chlorophyll-c2, chlorophyll-c1c2, chlorophyll-c3) in a known volume of any water body.

prefLabel._value: Concentration of total chlorophyll-a plus chlorophyll-b plus chlorophyll-c per unit volume of the water body

items.definition: The amount (mass or moles) of the following pigments (alloxanthin, diadinoxanthin, diatoxanthin, Zeaxanthin, alpha carotene, beta carotene) in a known volume of any water body.

prefLabel._value: Concentration of photoprotective carotenoids per unit volume of the water body

items.definition: The amount (mass or moles) of the following pigments (19-butanoyloxyfucoxanthin, fucoxanthin, 19-hexanoyloxyfucoxanthin, peridinin) in a known volume of any water body

prefLabel._value: Concentration of photosynthetic carotenoids per unit volume of the water body

items.definition: The amount (mass or moles) of photosynthetic carotenoids (19-butanoyloxyfucoxanthin, fucoxanthin, 19-hexanoyloxyfucoxanthin, peridinin) plus total chlorophyll-a pigments (divinyl chlorophyll-a, chlorophyll-a, chlorophyllide-a, chlorophyll-a allomers and chlorophyll-a prime) plus total chlorophyll-b pigments (divinyl chlorophyll-b, chlorophyll-b) plus total chlorophyll-c pigments (chlorophyll-c1, chlorophyll-c2, chlorophyll-c1c2, chlorophyll-c3) in a known volume of any water body.

prefLabel._value: Concentration of photosynthetic pigments per unit volume of the water body

items.definition: The amount (mass or moles) of photosynthetic carotenoids (19-butanoyloxyfucoxanthin, fucoxanthin, 19-hexanoyloxyfucoxanthin, peridinin) plus photoprotective carotenoids (alloxanthin, diadinoxanthin, diatoxanthin, Zeaxanthin, alpha carotene, beta carotene) plus total chlorophyll-b pigments (divinyl chlorophyll-b, chlorophyll-b) plus total chlorophyll-c pigments (chlorophyll-c1, chlorophyll-c2, chlorophyll-c1c2, chlorophyll-c3) in a known volume of any water body.

prefLabel._value: Concentration of total accessory pigments per unit volume of the water body

items.definition: Significant wave height approximated as four times the square root of the first moment of the wave power spectrum.

prefLabel._value: Spectral significant height of waves on the water body

items.definition: The amount (mass or moles) of all pigments in a known volume of any water body

prefLabel._value: Concentration of total pigment per unit volume of the water body

items.definition: The amount (mass or moles) of photosynthetic carotenoids (19-butanoyloxyfucoxanthin, fucoxanthin, 19-hexanoyloxyfucoxanthin, peridinin) plus total chlorophyll-b pigments (divinyl chlorophyll-b, chlorophyll-b) plus alloxanthin and zeaxanthin in a known volume of any water body.

prefLabel._value: Concentration of total diagnostic pigments per unit volume of the water body

items.definition: The volume of a biological object described elsewhere in the metadata (e.g.: single-species populations, all species within a phytoplankton sample …) occurring in a given volume of water.
